Volunteer Experiences

Intern | UNC Neurosurgery (Remote)

May - Aug. 2022

  • Met with other interns weekly to discuss medical school application process while receiving instruction on neuroscience topics and suture techniques

Intern | Casey Cares Foundation

Jun. - Aug. 2021

  • Packed and shipped care packages to dozens of Casey Cares families, contacting certain families over the phone to request address and contact information as needed
  • Used Raiser’s Edge NXT to organize contact information about Casey Cares families and store a record of what care packages contained
  • Organized and mailed hundreds of pajamas from annual pajama drive to local hospitals

Tutor | Boston University Community Service Center - Wizards

Dec. 2020 - May 2021

  • Created lesson plans and videos explaining various scientific topics through experimentation for local elementary, middle, and high schools with other tutors weekly

Blog Writer | Leading Women Tomorrow

Sep. 2020 - May 2021

  • Wrote for the nonprofit’s Boston University chapter about women and minorities in STEM being affected by impostor syndrome

Volunteer | Howard County General Hospital

Jul. - Aug 2019

  • Volunteered as part of the VolunTeen program for a total of 40 hours in the post-anesthesia care unit
  • Stocked and prepared beds for patients coming out of surgery and maintained an organized and clean front desk environment
) }
